<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Nepali Tea & Coffee Culture</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background: #f4f1ea;
            color: #333;
        }

        header {
            background: #5c3d2e;
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        nav {
            background: #8b5e3c;
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        nav a {
            color: white;
            margin: 0 15px;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        section {
            padding: 40px;
        }

        .hero {
            background: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1509042239860-f550ce710b93') no-repeat center/cover;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 100px 20px;
        }

        .card {
            background: white;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        footer {
            background: #5c3d2e;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 15px;
        }

        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            background: #c97b3a;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>☕ Nepali Tea & Coffee</h1>
    <p>Explore the taste of Nepal</p>
</header>

<nav>
    <a href="#about">About</a>
    <a href="#tea">Tea</a>
    <a href="#coffee">Coffee</a>
    <a href="#sugar">Sugar</a>
    <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
</nav>

<section class="hero">
    <h2>Fresh from the Hills of Nepal</h2>
    <p>Discover authentic tea & coffee culture</p>
    <a href="#tea" class="btn">Explore Now</a>
</section>

<section id="about">
    <h2>About</h2>
    <div class="card">
        <p>
            Nepal is famous for its rich tea gardens in Ilam and growing coffee farms in the hills.
            From traditional milk tea (chiya) to organic coffee, Nepal offers unique flavors loved by locals and tourists.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="tea">
    <h2>🍵 Tea (Chiya)</h2>
    <div class="card">
        <p>
            Nepali tea is known for its strong aroma and flavor. Popular types include:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Milk Tea (Dudh Chiya)</li>
            <li>Black Tea</li>
            <li>Green Tea</li>
            <li>Ilam Organic Tea</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="coffee">
    <h2>☕ Coffee</h2>
    <div class="card">
        <p>
            Coffee farming is growing in Nepal, especially in hilly regions.
            Nepali coffee is organic and has a smooth, mild taste.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="sugar">
    <h2>🍯 Sugar & Sweetness</h2>
    <div class="card">
        <p>
            Sugar plays a key role in Nepali beverages. Many people enjoy tea with a strong sweet taste.
            Alternatives like honey and jaggery are also popular.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="contact">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <div class="card">
        <p>Email: info@nepalitea.com</p>
        <p>Phone: +977-XXXXXXXXXX</p>
    </div>
</section>

<footer>
    <p>© 2026 Nepali Tea & Coffee Culture</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
